content:
To set up Service Catalog Guest Users:

The Service Catalog site requires the Service Catalog User permission set and a Channel Account license.

System Admin, Service Catalog Builder permissions, and membership in the site are needed to set up guest users.

This article applies to Aura and LWR Experience Sites.

Before you begin, ensure catalog items are enabled for guest user access and review Experience Cloud Help Articles on using Guest User profiles.

Step I: Create the Service Catalog Guest User Custom Permission Set
Create a new permission set with Service Catalog Guest Access license.
Save changes and enable Use Service Catalog For Guest User in System Permissions.

Step II: Configure the Guest User Profile for Service Catalog
Configure guest user profile to allow interaction without logging in.
Assign Service Catalog Guest User permission set to the guest user profile.

Step III: Configure Guest User Preferences
Allow guest users to access APIs in Experience Workspaces.
Save changes.

Step IV: Provide Guest User Access to Your Catalog Items
Grant guest users access to catalog items with autolaunched and orchestration flows.
title: Setting Up Service Catalog Guest Users in Salesforce
